<dl id="n53125k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53125k">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53125k"> 125(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> beggarbowl, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53125k"><li>FW 239.06 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kc/lexkc.htm#n53125k">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kc/l39kc.htm#n53125k">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53125k">MS BL 47477-284</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:419 <a name="kad9" href="../../FF/fdra/kda.htm#kcd8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kc/kcd8.htm#n53125k">Draft: II.1&sect;3.8</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Enfin, ils manqu&egrave;rent &agrave; leur convention. Tous, &agrave; la fois, se lev&egrave;rent; ils coururent vers le Bienheureux, ils le salu&egrave;rent. L&apos;un prit soin <mark>vase &agrave; aum&ocirc;nes</mark>, l&apos;autre son manteau; on lui pr&eacute;senta un si&egrave;ge. On lui apporta de l&apos;eau pour laver ses pieds. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 107</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The five disciples, reluctant at first, ran to meet the Buddha, took his coat and beggarbowl and offered him a seat. </mm> </dd></dl>
